<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Ah won't do it . . . but Ah sure feel like rootin a mob in one o those kitin frenzies when tha bard isn't payin attention . . . next rotation thru tha mob would eat him.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
This, however, would be a very BAD idea.  Because swarm kiting involves very light, proximity-only aggro to gather the swarm, (otherwise they won't aggro the pet), any form of &quot;Help&quot; from another will result in aggro transferring to YOU.  (Yes, I have seen druids try to &quot;help&quot; a swarming bard by snaring or healing, only to be rewarded with death!)<br>
